From 18880cdde8ed468945fc335fbf0061488ec9bb6a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Narendhar Reddy <nare@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Aug 2025 15:56:28 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP:cfg80211:fix incorrect channel check for non-beaconing interfaces

Reorder checks to allow off-channel operations for
non-beaconing interfaces. Currently, the logic returned
false and triggered warnings while checking operational chandef
for station.

[  122.770080] Call trace:
[  122.772522]  cfg80211_ch_switch_notify+0x3fc/0x4428 [cfg80211]
[  122.778371]  genl_family_rcv_msg_doit+0xc4/0x12c
[  122.782998]  genl_rcv_msg+0x1e0/0x268
[  122.786665]  netlink_rcv_skb+0x5c/0x128
[  122.790507]  genl_rcv+0x34/0x48

Signed-off-by: Narendhar Reddy <nare@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/wireless/nl80211.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/nl80211.c b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
index 1d2aa59..3fb2d7f 100644
--- a/net/wireless/nl80211.c
+++ b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
@@ -10779,12 +10779,12 @@ static bool cfg80211_off_channel_oper_allowed(struct wireless_dev *wdev,
 
 	lockdep_assert_wiphy(wdev->wiphy);
 
-	if (!cfg80211_wdev_channel_allowed(wdev, chan))
-		return false;
-
 	if (!cfg80211_beaconing_iface_active(wdev))
 		return true;
 
+	if (!cfg80211_wdev_channel_allowed(wdev, chan))
+		return false;
+
 	radio_idx = cfg80211_get_hw_idx_by_chan(wdev->wiphy, chan);
 
 	/*
-- 
2.34.1

